This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommendation systems, which are a common application of collaborative filtering in information retrieval. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a probabilistic framework for modeling the rating problem. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as collaborative filtering is a popular technique in AI for building recommendation systems. The paper also involves the use of probabilistic matrix factorization, which is a common technique in Statistical Inference (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
